Why come to St. Louis in the winter? The southern beaches are beautiful, but St. Louis showcases some of it s most unique opportunities in the cold weather. Here are some of the unique winter activities our city has to offer:
    Gateway Arch National Park Museum. Riding to the top of      the arch in the winter affords amazing views, especially with snow on the      ground!  Union Station that houses St. Louis  newest addition,      the Aquarium.   City Museum. 600,000 square feet of unique indoor      entertainment. City Museum offers MonstroCity, The World s Largest Jungle      Gym; five-story and ten-story spiral slides in the Shoe Shafts; the      Enchanted Caves; Everyday Circus and the Cabin Inn. This is a great      activity for kids and grown ups alike!   Indoor activities at Forest Park: The St. Louis Art      Museum, St. Louis Science Center, James S. McDonnell Planetarium, and the      Missouri History Museum.   St Louis also has several incredible indoor museums:      The Magic House Children s Museum, Sachs Butterfly House, Myseum, Museum      of Transportation.   Want to enjoy the cold? How about Hidden Valley Ski      Resort or ice staking in the largest outdoor skating rink in the Midwest,      Steinberg Skating Rink in Forest Park?   If the cold isn t your thing, St. Louis offers an amazing culinary scene with incredible restaurants, craft breweries and large scale breweries.


